Duration, Film table

Here and below unless noted: entries with NA YearOfProduction removed, impossible years and future removed. Plots with duplicates removed: duplicates in concatenation of TitleVA_YearOfProduction_Duration removed (preferring entries with fewer NAs and if equal then later upload date); then 50325 left. Plots with no duplicate removal: just the impossible years (upload date before the platform existed, film produced before film existed) filters.

Genre

The following plots: there’s sometimes multiple genres, languages, countries per film, I’m summing all of them below; so in principle a film with many labels can have a bit more effect on the summary than one with single tags.

I’m going to lowercase all the categories, as sometimes capitalization varies.

Filtering: there’s a bunch of refFilm IDs here that don’t occur in the Film table; 145828 compared to the full table; 204137 after filtering out duplicates and films with impossible date or length as discussed above. I’m going to filter out what I’m assuming are the duplicates (not in terms of what appears here multiple times i.e. multi-genre, but what appears in the Film table as multiple times) in this and the following sections. For the idxFilmKind table, that entails keeping about 14% of the original table, but should provide a more objective view.

What type of entity enters a film for sale

dbo.idxFilmRole table What type of entity enters a film for sale: connect to Film through refFilm column, entity type info from lstRole column. Categories are listed below. These come from the dbo.Menu table, column Libelle: 26001: Sales 26002: Distributor 26003: Producer 26004: Financier 26005: Festival 26006: Promotion 26007: Buyers’ Rep 26008: Consultant 26009: Broadcaster
